<HEADLINE> Tony Awards To Add Category  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Tony Awards next season will add a category
to honor ''special theatrical events,'' Broadway presentations that
don't fit into the existing 21 categories for musicals, plays and
revivals.
</P>
<P>
   The Tony Awards Administration Committee decided on the new
category Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''With many new forms of entertainment being produced on
Broadway, the committee felt the current categories were not
sufficient to address the changes we are seeing in the theater,''
said Roy A. Somlyo, president of the American Theater Wing.
</P>
<P>
   Had the award existed this season, Broadway offerings that might
have been considered in the category include the Irish dance
spectacle ''Riverdance'' or ''Dame Edna: The Royal Tour,'' which is
comedy -- the ''dame'' is Australian actor Barry Humphries in drag --
with audience participation.
</P>
<P>
   The American Theater Wing and League of American Theaters and
Producers present the Tony Awards, which this year will be given
June 4.
</P>
<P>
   PBS and CBS will televise the event from Radio City Music Hall
with host Rosie O'Donnell.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
