<HEADLINE> Black Sea Polluted With Sewerage  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) -- About 2.1 million gallons of human waste
poured into the Black Sea after a sewer pipe broke in the port city
of Sevastopol, emergency officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The pipe ruptured Wednesday evening. Officials halted sewer
system pumps and diverted the flow into the sea until repairs could
be completed Thursday, the Emergency Situations Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
   It was the second sewer failure in Sevastopol since February,
when the city's main sewer pipe broke, sending waste into the sea.
</P>
