<HEADLINE> Chris Mihm Signs With Agent  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- Texas center Chris Mihm signed with an
agent Thursday, insuring the 7-footer will not return for his
senior season.
</P>
<P>
   Mihm signed with Octagon, which also represents David Robinson,
Jerry Stackhouse and Sheryl Swoopes. Jeff Austin, Octagon senior
vice president of basketball, will be the lead negotiator.
</P>
<P>
   Considered the best pure center in college basketball last
season, Mihm is projected as a top-five pick in the June 28 NBA
draft.
</P>
<P>
   Mihm averaged nearly 18 points and 10.5 rebounds in leading the
Longhorns to a 24-9 record. He holds the school record with 264
career blocks and ranks second with 945 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Underclassmen have until June 21 to pull out of the draft if
they have not signed with an agent.
</P>
<P>
   Mihm is just the second Longhorn to leave school early for the
NBA. LaSalle Thompson left after his junior season in 1982 and was
drafted by the Kansas City Kings with the No. 5 pick, which remains
the highest draft selection of a Texas player.
</P>
</TEXT>
