<HEADLINE> Public Funeral Set for Sealy Friday  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Malik Sealy's family, teammates and friends
planned to gather Friday for the funeral of the Minnesota
Timberwolves player killed last weekend in a head-on crash in
Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   The public service was scheduled for 10 a.m. at Riverside
Church, an interdenominational Christian church in Manhattan.
</P>
<P>
   The man charged with three counts of vehicular homicide in
Sealy's death had his first court appearance postponed Thursday
because he was still hospitalized. It was rescheduled for Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators have said Souksangouane Phengsene, 43, of
Minneapolis, was driving the wrong way on Minnesota Highway 100
early Saturday morning when his pickup smashed into Sealy's sport
utility truck.
</P>
<P>
   The 30-year-old player who helped the Timberwolves post their
best season in franchise history this year was returning from a
birthday celebration for teammate Kevin Garnett.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors said Phengsene had a blood-alcohol level of nearly
twice the legal limit. Sealy also had been drinking before the
crash, but his blood alcohol level was .08 percent, within the
legal limit of .10.
</P>
