<HEADLINE> Arrest Made in Insider Trading Case  </HEADLINE>
By LARRY NEUMEISTER
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- An X-rated movie actress who allegedly got
inside stock tips from the chief executive of a respected Wall
Street company has been arrested in Canada.
</P>
<P>
   Kathryn B. Gannon, known as ''Marylin Star'' in X-rated movies
and publications, was arrested on insider trading charges Wednesday
at her Vancouver, British Columbia, residence, according to U.S.
Attorney Mary Jo White.
</P>
<P>
   Gannon appeared in a Canadian court Thursday and was released on
$50,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Gannon, 31, had been a fugitive since she was charged in
December along with James McDermott Jr., the former chief executive
officer at Keefe, Bruyette &AMP; Woods, a firm that specialized in bank
mergers.
</P>
<P>
   McDermott was convicted last month of securities fraud for
giving Gannon inside information, prompting her to allegedly buy
six stocks illegally. She was accused of then giving the
information to a third defendant, Anthony Pomponio, who also was
convicted in the conspiracy. Both men were having extramarital
affairs with Gannon at the time, lawyers in the case have said.
</P>
<P>
   Pomponio and Gannon allegedly made $170,000 in illegal profits.
</P>
<P>
   Howard Shapiro, Gannon's lawyer, did not immediately return a
telephone message for comment.
</P>
<P>
   He said after McDermott's conviction that the verdict did not
mean his client is guilty of the conspiracy and securities fraud
charges.
</P>
<P>
   ''Indeed, she is not and she intends to contest them
vigorously,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
